{{ thought_balloon }} <b>Update pyTMBot with Docker Compose</b>

These steps apply if you run pyTMBot with Docker Compose and the service is named <code>pytmbot</code>.
If your path or service name is different, adjust the commands below.

<b>Recommended steps:</b>

1) Open the directory with your <code>compose.yaml</code>
2) Pull the latest image
3) Recreate the service
4) Check status and recent logs

<pre>cd /opt/pytmbot
docker compose pull pytmbot
docker compose up -d --force-recreate pytmbot
docker compose ps
docker compose logs -n 50 pytmbot</pre>

<b>Optional cleanup:</b>
<code>docker image prune -f</code>

ℹ️ <i>Your mounted config and secret files stay in place.</i>
